verses.verse: Prayse ye the Lorde, prayse ye the Lord in his sanctuarie: praise ye him in the firmament of his power.
Prayse ye hym in his strength: prayse ye hym in his excellent greatnesse.
Prayse ye hym in the sounde of a trumpet: prayse ye hym vpon a Lute and an Harpe.
Prayse ye hym with a tabret and a daunce: prayse ye him vpon the stringes and vpon the Organes.
Prayse ye hym vpon the well tuned Cimbales: prayse ye hym vpon the loude Cimbales.
Euery thyng that draweth breath: ought to prayse the Lorde. Prayse ye the Lorde.
